Numerical Differentiation Methods in Excel
Overview
This project demonstrates the implementation of several **numerical differentiation methods** using **Microsoft Excel** to approximate the derivative of a mathematical function from discrete data points.
The project compares different finite difference approaches to observe how each method estimates the derivative and to understand their computational characteristics. It also includes a function graph for better visualization of the analyzed data.

Objectives
- Implement numerical differentiation using Microsoft Excel.
- Apply several finite difference methods.
- Compare numerical approximation results.
- Visualize the function using charts.
- Understand the characteristics of different differentiation methods.

Methods
The following finite difference methods are implemented:
- Forward Difference O(h)
- Backward Difference O(h)
- Central Difference O(h²)
- Forward Difference O(h²)

Results
The numerical approximations obtained from each method are:
| Method | Approximation |
|---------|--------------:|
| Forward Difference O(h) | -0.5486650000 |
| Backward Difference O(h) | -0.3104710000 |
| Central Difference O(h²) | -0.4295680000 |
| Forward Difference O(h²) | -0.3994257500 |
The comparison shows that each finite difference method produces a different approximation value. This demonstrates that the choice of numerical differentiation method should be based on the characteristics of the mathematical problem and the required level of accuracy.

